<TITLE> New Zealand win toss, bowl first against Sri Lanka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 GALLE, Sri Lanka, Aug 18 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - New Zealand won the toss and chose to bowl first against Sri Lanka after early rain delayed the start of the first Test on Tuesday. Sri Lanka dropped opener Malinda Warnapura and promoted Tillakaratne Dilshan from the middle order into the opening spot after he recovered from a finger injury. The match started 90 minutes late and a total of 83 overs are scheduled for the day. Sri Lanka: Kumar Sangakkara (captain), Tillakaratne Dilshan, Tharanga Paranavitana, Mahela Jayawardene, Thilan Samaraweera, Prasanna Jayawardene, Angelo Mathews, Muthiah Muralitharan, Ajantha Mendis, Thilan Thushara, Nuwan Kulasekara New Zealand: Daniel Vettori (captain), Tim McIntosh, Martin Guptill, Daniel Flynn, Ross Taylor, Jesse Ryder, Brendon McCullum, Jacob Oram, Jeetan Patel, Iain O'Brien, Chris Martin. 
